			<content:encoded><![CDATA[<div>So, I started watching this a few days ago and I am pleasantly surprised by how good it is. They really do keep to the feel of the original movies, complete with the Noah character who acts as the know it all voice of the audience to exclaim how silly some of the stuff is. For the most part, they handle the situations very realistically, with the notable exception of the lack of media coverage later on in the run. Seriously, half a dozen high school kids are murdered in around 3-4 weeks and no major media comes around to cover it?<br />
<br />
Anyway, if you want to see a slasher flick (well, more of a mystery really) that is pretty well done check it out.</div>

